From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 07:22:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== core parameter validation ====

mm/damon: validate parameters in the core

DAMON has a number of parameters.  Some of the parameters are validated
by DAMON, while some are validated by DAMON API callers.  There is no
clear central point of validation.  As a result, it is easy to make
mistakes at validations.  Actually we recently found a few bugs of this
class.

DAMON sysfs interface is a caller that is believed to doing the most
complete parameters validation.  It uses a test purpose
damon_ctx_commit() call, which is a DAMON core function that is believed
(who knows, it might have some bugs) to doing all parameter validations.

Embed the validation mechanism inside the DAMON core functions that
receive parameters: damon_start() and damon_commit_ctx().  Also, remove
parameter validations in callers that are no more required.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
